      <section eId="sec_3205">
        <num>3205</num>
        <heading>Attendance of minors upon full time day instruction</heading>
        <subsection eId="sec_3205__subsec_i">
          <num>(i)</num>
          <content>
            <p>Minors whose parents elect not to enroll their children in school\nuntil the following September.\n  (ii) Students enrolled in non-public schools or in home instruction.\n  3. In each school district, the board of education shall have power to\nrequire minors from sixteen to seventeen years of age who are not\nemployed to attend upon full time day instruction until the last day of\nsession in the school year in which the student becomes seventeen years\nof age.\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
      </section>
